    {
      "id": "aec2a23aca810b54ea55cf7ece423aa67d961eda",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-10-10 09:44:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nThis patch unfortunately failed with the same symptoms as LU-5121, which was marked as ad implicate if LU-5077, so it clearly didn't fix the problem. It is worthwhile to investigate this new test failure to see what the symptoms are in this case.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "0d51858709c2c4cdc5a29fd6f90749879ac1a270",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2014-10-10 15:18:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.5/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/f928a584-5087-11e4-ac0f-5254006e85c2).  Ran 19 tests.  2 tests failed: sanity-lfsck, conf-sanity.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "48393c17a9fe37c014ded843ac207e18c111a654",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 104,
        "name": "Niu Yawei",
        "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
        "username": "niu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-10-11 07:53:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nLooks the new OOM happened on a non-lustre process, and the slab_unreclaimable is still very high. I didn't find any other useful information.\n\nProbably we need to enable D_MALLOC for all these tests which could trigger OOM, and print out slabinfo after each test case, so that we may find out whcih slab is holding so much memory, however, seems maloo isn't able to capture debug log for such OOM failure (all debug logs for these failures are empty), is there some TEI ticket for this?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5709b9cdd87b5d36ca776ea215da4ea6b1935b08",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-10-20 01:00:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nSince it has been verified that the OOM issue is not related with crypto API, this patch is unnecessary. Then mark it as \"-1\".",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "936016fbbdb3f94ed89f5af6e5ab9a5ee8d09277",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-10-20 06:50:50.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI'd actually prefer to still land this patch.  It reduces the memory usage and complexity of the code.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "85448ad648a5dad2ad3800a03e7ed17017c94be7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-10-20 07:41:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> I'd actually prefer to still land this patch. It reduces the memory usage and complexity of the code.\n\nThat means the patch http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/3098/ will be partly reverted, or the benefit mentioned in such patch comment will be broken.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e3030db843853cdd6ebaa123da6e0c8026ec0539",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 104,
        "name": "Niu Yawei",
        "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
        "username": "niu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-10-20 09:56:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAndreas, looks this isn't only used for early reply, it's also used for ldlm lock callbacks. Given that's rarely used, I agree with Fanyong that we'd keep it as-is but not introducing new changes.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
